From: OpenVDB Contributors
Subject: [PATCH] Rewrite xcode_locator.m for macOS 10.6 compatibility

This patch rewrites xcode_locator.m to:
1. Remove ARC requirement - use manual retain/release
2. Replace LSCopyApplicationURLsForBundleIdentifier (10.10+) with
   directory scanning of /Applications and /Developer
3. Remove modern ObjC literal syntax for GCC compatibility
4. Support building with GCC (gcc-14 or similar)

On macOS 10.6, Xcode lives in /Developer or /Applications/Xcode.app.
This version scans known locations instead of using Launch Services.

---
 tools/osx/xcode_locator.m | 298 +++++++++++++++++-----------------------------
 1 file changed, 107 insertions(+), 191 deletions(-)

